Implement `chipper sort` — interactive binary search insertion sort for unsorted tickets.

Algorithm (per unsorted ticket):
- Show the ticket being sorted alongside the queue's current midpoint ticket
- User chooses which is higher priority
- Recurse into the appropriate half of the list
- Once the candidate segment is fewer than 10 tickets, show the full segment;
  user may continue with midpoint comparisons or pick an exact insertion index directly
- Insert the ticket at the chosen position in chipper-queue using the sparse index scheme

`chipper new` triggers this automatically after ticket creation.
`chipper sort` runs it for all currently unsorted tickets.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation
